{
  "id": "asm-banking",
  "kind": "problem",
  "title": "Progressive Banking Ledger",
  "difficulty": "medium",
  "concepts": [
    "simulation",
    "stateful design",
    "hash map",
    "scheduling"
  ],
  "prompt": "Implement a small ledger driven by an operation list. `solution(queries)` receives a list of queries; each query is a list of strings `[OP, timestamp, ...args]`. Every query carries a non-negative integer `timestamp` (given as a string), even when this level doesn't use it. Return a list with one string result per query, in order. All amounts are non-negative integers in **cents** (given as strings).\n\n**Level 1 operations**\n\n- `[\"CREATE_ACCOUNT\", timestamp, account]` — create a new account with zero balance. Return `\"true\"`, or `\"false\"` if the account already exists.\n- `[\"DEPOSIT\", timestamp, account, amount]` — add `amount` cents to `account`. Return the new balance as a string, or `\"\"` if the account does not exist.\n- `[\"WITHDRAW\", timestamp, account, amount]` — subtract `amount` cents from `account`. Return the new balance as a string, or `\"\"` if the account does not exist or the withdrawal would overdraw it (no change in that case).\n- `[\"TRANSFER\", timestamp, source, target, amount]` — move `amount` cents from `source` to `target`. Return `source`'s new balance as a string, or `\"\"` if either account is missing, source equals target, or source would be overdrawn (no change in those cases).\n\nLater levels add operations to the same function, so structure it as a clean per-op dispatcher and keep all balances as integer cents.",
  "signature": {
    "name": "solution",
    "inputs": [
      {
        "name": "queries",
        "type": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "output": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    }
  },
